
[1]civility

   CIVILITY, n.

   1. The state of being civilized; refinement of manners; applied to
   nations; as distinguished from the rudeness of barbarous nations.

   2. Good breeding; politeness; complaisance; courtesy; decorum of
   behavior in the treatment of others, accompanied with kind offices, and
   attention to their wants and desires. Civility respects manners or
   external deportment, and in the plural, civilities denote acts of
   politeness.
